tldr: The agent successfully reviewed the sleep questionnaire application
  against the provided specification and Statement of Work. It then implemented
  all identified missing features, including a tiredness severity scale, COMISA
  detection, insufficient sleep syndrome detection, outbound resource links,
  weighted EDS scoring, full CSV export, pain and chronic fatigue screening, and
  medical/mental health history sections.
overview: The user initiated a comprehensive review of their sleep questionnaire
  application, seeking to validate its adherence to the Statement of Work and
  detailed specifications, and to implement any identified missing features. The
  agent systematically addressed each requirement, enhancing the application's
  diagnostic capabilities and data reporting. Key implementations included a
  granular 1-10 tiredness severity scale with critical safety alerts, advanced
  detection for complex sleep disorders like COMISA and Insufficient Sleep
  Syndrome, and the integration of valuable external resource links. The data
  export functionality was significantly improved to provide a complete,
  flattened view of all questionnaire responses. Furthermore, the agent added
  crucial screening for pain-related sleep issues and chronic fatigue, alongside
  sections for comprehensive medical and mental health history. This structured
  approach ensured all specified criteria were met, significantly enriching the
  application's functionality and user experience.
